'''阿滕伯勒自然保护区'''是英格兰[[诺丁汉郡|诺丁汉郡]]{{le|阿滕伯勒|Attenborough, Nottinghamshire}}的[[自然保护区|自然保护区]]，位于诺丁汉市中心西南部{{convert|7|km|abbr=on|order=flip}}处，<ref name="Broxtowe">{{cite web|url=http://www.broxtowe.gov.uk/index.aspx?articleid=2178 |title=Attenborough Nature Reserve : Broxtowe Borough Council |publisher=Broxtowe Borough Council |accessdate=2011-09-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120610135403/http://www.broxtowe.gov.uk/index.aspx?articleid=2178 |archivedate=2012-06-10 }}</ref>归{{le|诺丁汉郡野生动物基金会|Nottinghamshire Wildlife Trust}}所有<ref name="ANC-About-R">{{cite web|url=http://www.attenboroughnaturecentre.co.uk/about/attenborough-nature-reserve/|title=Attenborough Nature Reserve About|publisher=Nottinghamshire Wildlife Trust|accessdate=2011-09-04|archive-date=2014-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140322102539/http://www.attenboroughnaturecentre.co.uk/about/attenborough-nature-reserve|dead-url=no}}</ref>，由布罗克斯托议会赞助。<ref name="Broxtowe" /><ref name="ANC-About-R" />它们以一百万[[英镑|英镑]]在2020年将其购得。阿滕伯勒自然中心设于其中心位置，包含旅客服务与教育设施。<ref name="ANC">{{cite web|url=http://www.attenboroughnaturecentre.co.uk/|title=Attenborough Nature Centre|publisher=Nottinghamshire Wildlife Trust|accessdate=2011-09-04| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110725130952/http://www.attenboroughnaturecentre.co.uk/| archivedate= 2011-07-25}}</ref>

== 历史 ==

该区域在1929年至1967年之间被一家砾石开采公司（CEMEX）用作砾石坑，公司从附近开采砾石和沙子，砾石运输船会穿越该区域。<ref name="Broxtowe" />砾石坑在经过处理后恢复为湿地，其中包含2010年恢复的施林普顿处土地。<ref>[http://www.cemexcommunities.co.uk/thrumptons-land.html Cemex communities website: Thrumpton's Land] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cemexcommunities.co.uk/thrumptons-land.html |date=20160304055112 }}. [2012-03-18]</ref>

2019年年末，土地持有者宣布出售土地，并获得了当地[[戴維·阿滕伯勒|戴維·阿滕伯勒]]的支持。他筹集了所需的一百万英镑，将其所有权转让给诺丁汉郡野生动物基金会，基金会帮他维护了这片土地六十年。<ref name="BBC Nov 25">[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-nottinghamshire-50539487 Sir David Attenborough backs £1m nature reserve appeal] {{Wayback|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-nottinghamshire-50539487 |date=20201030042216 }} ''[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] Nottingham'', 2019-11-25. [2020-01-16]</ref><ref name="Post Nov 26">[https://www.nottinghampost.com/news/local-news/notts-wildlife-trust-launches-urgent-3572237 Notts Wildlife Trust launches 'urgent' £1m appeal to buy Attenborough Nature Reserve] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nottinghampost.com/news/local-news/notts-wildlife-trust-launches-urgent-3572237 |date=20201102063253 }} ''Nottingham Post'', 2019-11-26. [2020-01-16].</ref>

== 地理 ==

阿滕伯勒自然保护区位于{{le|埃里沃什河|River Erewash}}和[[特倫特河|特倫特河]]的交汇处，现有145公顷的湖泊、湿地、草原和灌木丛，<ref name="ANC-About-R" />它是具有[[具特殊科學價值地點_(英國)|特殊科学兴趣]]的阿滕伯勒砾石坑的一部分。<ref>{{cite web|title=Attenborough Gravel Pits SSSI citation |url=http://designatedsites.naturalengland.org.uk/PDFsForWeb/Citation/1003408.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304040717/http://www.sssi.naturalengland.org.uk/citation/citation_photo/1003408.pdf |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}</ref>砾石坑的面积为{{convert|226.6|ha|acres}}，向西延伸至保护区外，直至县境。<ref name="ANC-About-R" />

淹没的坑形成了多个大湖，如教堂湖、克利夫顿湖等<ref>[http://www.attenboroughnaturecentre.co.uk/docs/Map-for-website.jpg Attenborough Nature Centre Map of the reserve.] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110809211611/http://www.attenboroughnaturecentre.co.uk/docs/Map-for-website.jpg |date=2011-08-09 }} [2012-03-18]</ref>，其周围还有柳树林。<ref name="ANC-About-R" />这些湖是诺丁汉郡鸟类过冬的地区，自1966年以来栖息着超过250种鸟。<ref name="ANC-About-R" />可以在保护区看到的当地稀有鸟类有[[攀雀|攀雀]]（1994）、[[白翅黄池鹭|白翅黄池鹭]]（1998，2011）、[[草鹭|草鹭]]（2003）和{{le|黑脸田鸡|sora (bird)}}（2004）。<ref name="NBW">{{cite web |url=http://www.nottsbirders.net/attenborough.html |title=Attenborough Nature Reserve |date=2015-12-01 |publisher=Nottinghamshire Birdwatchers |accessdate=2019-04-29 |archive-date=2017-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171221141544/http://www.nottsbirders.net/attenborough.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 设施 ==
保护区内的阿滕伯勒自然中心设有教育设施、商店、休闲区和停车场，该中心在2005年完工，因生态旅游获得金奖。<ref>[http://www.attenboroughnaturecentre.co.uk/about/ About the Attenborough Nature Centre] {{Wayback|url=http://www.attenboroughnaturecentre.co.uk/about/ |date=20140320182927 }}. Attenborough Nature Centre. [2012-03-18]</ref>《{{le|BBC野生动物|BBC Wildlife}}》的一篇文章将其列为世界十大生态场所之排名第九。<ref name="ANC"/><ref>[http://www.greentraveller.co.uk/node/45 Green Traveller blog] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111224215316/http://www.greentraveller.co.uk/node/45 |date=2011-12-24 |accessdate=2012-03-18}}</ref>
